text: Kristee Porter (born May 7, 1980) is a United States volleyball player, and coach. She participated at the 2002 FIVB World Grand Prix. She played for University of California, Los Angeles. She coached for University of Colorado, Navarro College, and Robert E. Lee High School. On November 1, 2019, Porter will be inducted into the UCLA Athletics Hall of Fame as a three-sport participant.
